  "local_port": 58406,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What marks are required in the IISER aptitude test in order to get admission in any of the IISERs? Also, what rank in the JEE (Advanced) is good enough?",
  "response": "To get admission into any of the Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISERs), you can apply through one of the two channels: the IISER Aptitude Test (IAT) or through the rank obtained in the JEE (Advanced). Here are the details for both:\n\n### IISER Aptitude Test (IAT)\n1. **Eligibility Criteria**: You must have passed Class XII (or equivalent) exam with science stream in the current year or the previous year.\n2. **Marks Required**: \n   - You need to score above the cut-off marks, which vary each year based on the difficulty of the exam and the number of applicants. Generally, the cut-off is around 80-90 out of 240.\n   - You are then ranked based on your score, and seats are allocated according to this rank in the counseling process.\n\n### JEE (Advanced)\n1. **Eligibility Criteria**: You must have a rank in the Common Rank List (CRL) of JEE (Advanced).\n2. **Rank Required**:\n   - A rank within the top 10,000 in the CRL of JEE (Advanced) is generally considered good enough to secure admission into any of the IISERs. However, the exact cut-off rank can vary each year.\n   - Some IISERs may have slightly different cut-offs, so it\u2019s advisable to check the specific requirements of each institute.\n\n### Additional Information\n- **Counseling**: After qualifying through either the IAT or JEE (Advanced), you will need to participate in the counseling process where you can select your preferred IISER.\n- **Seat Allocation**: Seats are allocated based on your rank and your preferences during the counseling process.\n\nIt's essential to stay updated with the official IISER websites and notifications for the most accurate and current information regarding admission criteria and cut-offs.",
